message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Malta in the past 20 years is the assassination of journalist Daphne Caruana Galizia in 2017. Caruana Galizia was a prominent investigative journalist known for her work exposing corruption and malpractice in Maltese politics and business. Her murder shocked the nation and sparked widespread protests and calls for justice. The event brought international attention to issues of press freedom and corruption in Malta, leading to significant political and legal reforms in the country.
